29/02/2008
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The US consulate in Banja Luka announced its re-opening in a statement Thursday (February 28th), a week after demonstrations against Kosovo's independence turned violent in the Bosnian Serb capital. 
Young protestors attacked the US and other diplomatic missions in Republika Srpska, after seeing an attack on the US Embassy in Belgrade. 
Five policemen were injured and 27 protestors were detained. 
(RTRS, NTV Hayat, AFP - 28/02/08)
